<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-468-530  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 468 530.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 21 1990 n368 p115(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Nationals continue to offer strong incentive programs; regionalsresist, citing smaller number of vendors. (national distributors)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shalvoy, Mary Lee.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>National distributors, such as Ingram Micro D and Softsel ComputerProducts Inc, continue to offer vendors strong incentive programsto encourage sales.andP;  Typically, when a reseller buys a vendor'sproduct, the reseller earns points.andP;  The reseller collects pointsto receive gift merchandise, such as a television or videocassetterecorder.andP;  The larger nationals have created incentive programswith detailed plans.andP;  On the other hand, regional distributorshave avoided using these programs, citing reasons such as a morefocused product mix and a smaller number of vendors.andP;  Someregional distributors believe that most dealers do not want to belocked into a program because they purchase a variety of productsfrom different vendors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DistributorsValue-Added ResellersSales ManagementIncentivesMarketing StrategyRegionalComputer Retailing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>